Hey, guys, come on!

248
00:19:08,482 --> 00:19:09,525
SAM:
Let's go!

249
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:12,569
PETER: Sam, just get back on the bus.
We can talk about it.

250
00:19:12,778 --> 00:19:14,738
Molly, Sam, come on, guys.

251
00:19:19,409 --> 00:19:21,203
Did he seem weird to you
when he got on the bus?

252
00:19:21,411 --> 00:19:23,121
No, he was fine. It's like he just snapped.

253
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:25,999
-What's going on?
-What the hell is going on out here?

254
00:19:31,255 --> 00:19:34,258
[CABLES SNAPPING]

255
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,218
DENNIS:
We should, uh....

256
00:19:36,426 --> 00:19:37,553
ISAAC:
Holy shit!

257
00:19:37,761 --> 00:19:39,263
DENNIS:
Get off the bus!

258
00:19:40,681 --> 00:19:43,934
[CROWD SCREAMING]

259
00:19:54,319 --> 00:19:55,362
SAM:
Come on!

260
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,260
How did you know?

261
00:20:27,144 --> 00:20:28,812
MAN:
That's the big question here.

262
00:20:29,688 --> 00:20:31,273
How did you know?

263
00:20:32,482 --> 00:20:34,109
It says right here in your statement:

264
00:20:34,318 --> 00:20:37,863
"I saw it collapse.
I knew it would happen."

265
00:20:38,071 --> 00:20:39,615
That sounds premeditated to me.

266
00:20:39,823 --> 00:20:41,700
No, no, no. That's not what I meant.

267
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:46,330
I had a vision.

268
00:20:46,788 --> 00:20:49,291
Okay. A vision.

269
00:20:49,499 --> 00:20:52,461
Psychic phenomena, ghosts, Bigfoot.

270
00:20:52,669 --> 00:20:54,588
You actually believe in that stuff?

271
00:20:54,796 --> 00:20:55,839
I don't know.

272
00:20:58,425 --> 00:21:00,302
I'll tell you what I believe:

273
00:21:00,511 --> 00:21:02,304
There's an answer for everything.

274
00:21:02,513 --> 00:21:04,973
There's an answer for why
you knew to warn everyone...

275
00:21:05,182 --> 00:21:08,644
...the bridge was going to collapse,
and minutes later, it did.

276
00:21:08,852 --> 00:21:13,106
I told you, I saw it coming.
I don't know how.

277
00:21:13,315 --> 00:21:14,608
I just did.

278
00:21:16,443 --> 00:21:18,320
And no one else did?

279
00:21:18,529 --> 00:21:22,157
Like I said, it just came out of nowhere.

280
00:21:22,366 --> 00:21:23,909
Did Sam have issues with authority?

281
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:27,829
Did he ever demonstrate
any sort of extremist behavior?

282
00:21:28,038 --> 00:21:29,206
No.

283
00:21:30,707 --> 00:21:33,460
Wait. "Extremist behavior"?

284
00:21:33,919 --> 00:21:35,671
You mean like a terrorist?

285
00:21:35,879 --> 00:21:39,341
You see him talk to anyone that morning?
On a cell phone, pay phone?

286
00:21:39,550 --> 00:21:40,884
Just his girlfriend.

287
00:21:41,468 --> 00:21:44,513
His ex-girlfriend, I mean. Molly.

288
00:21:44,721 --> 00:21:47,558
-But that was in person.
-Molly.

289
00:21:48,725 --> 00:21:49,768
Ex.

290
00:21:49,977 --> 00:21:51,520
BLOCK:
Tell me about the breakup.

291
00:21:51,728 --> 00:21:55,732
Was he upset? Scale of 1 to 10.

292
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:57,901
It's personal.

293
00:21:59,152 --> 00:22:02,739
You must have been pissed, right?
Getting dumped like that.

294
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:04,908
What does that have to do
with anything?

295
00:22:05,284 --> 00:22:07,953
I'm just trying to get all the pieces
of the puzzle together...

296
00:22:08,161 --> 00:22:11,331
...before I start moving them around,
making them fit.

297
00:22:11,748 --> 00:22:16,879
Look, I just had a hunch that something
bad was gonna happen. That's it.

298
00:22:17,087 --> 00:22:18,422
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

299
00:22:19,381 --> 00:22:20,924
Excuse me.

300
00:22:24,094 --> 00:22:26,138
Forensics came back with the analysis.

301
00:22:26,930 --> 00:22:28,974
-And?
-They're chalking it up to high winds...

302
00:22:29,183 --> 00:22:31,059
...and structural damage
from the construction.

303
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:32,561
"High winds"?

304
00:22:32,769 --> 00:22:34,771
AGENT:
Yeah. Send everyone home.

305
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,482
You're free to go.

306
00:22:44,031 --> 00:22:47,242
I have a feeling
we'll be seeing each other again.

307
00:22:47,451 --> 00:22:48,785
Call it a hunch.

308
00:22:56,293 --> 00:22:59,338
WOMAN [ON TV]: Authorities are calling
the North Bay Bridge collapse...

309
00:22:59,546 --> 00:23:01,256
...a freak act of nature...

310
00:23:01,465 --> 00:23:06,094
...citing a highway improvement project
that may have weakened the superstructure.

311
00:23:06,303 --> 00:23:10,265
Among the survivors were eight employees
of Presage Paper...

312
00:23:10,474 --> 00:23:12,434
...on their way to a business retreat.

313
00:23:12,643 --> 00:23:15,938
The other 17 employees
were killed in the collapse.

314
00:23:16,146 --> 00:23:18,982
And although they've been branded
the "lucky eight"...

315
00:23:19,191 --> 00:23:23,320
...the surviving employees
now face an uncertain future.

316
00:23:43,173 --> 00:23:44,341
NATHAN:
Hey, guys.

317
00:23:44,550 --> 00:23:45,634
MOLLY:
Hey.

318
00:23:45,843 --> 00:23:46,885
PETER:
Hey.

319
00:23:48,387 --> 00:23:51,682
Anybody know
when this thing's supposed to start?

320
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:55,227
When Dennis gets here, I guess.

321
00:23:57,020 --> 00:23:58,689
That agent still hounding you?

322
00:23:59,231 --> 00:24:03,360
No. You heard the news,
it was natural causes.

323
00:24:04,069 --> 00:24:05,696
Yeah, more like supernatural.

324
00:24:07,239 --> 00:24:09,908
How you holding up? I tried calling.

325
00:24:10,117 --> 00:24:13,453
No, yeah, I saw. I was just tired.

326
00:24:15,497 --> 00:24:16,707
ISAAC:
So?

327
00:24:18,375 --> 00:24:20,043
How did you explain it?

328
00:24:22,921 --> 00:24:24,214
I didn't.

329
00:24:25,382 --> 00:24:26,425
I couldn't.

330
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:28,343
Sam, there had to be a reason.

331
00:24:28,552 --> 00:24:30,971
Heh. That is exactly
what the agent kept saying.

332
00:24:35,225 --> 00:24:38,562
Whatever answer you're looking for,
I don't have it.

333
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:41,064
Yeah, Sam's right.
It doesn't matter how it happened.

334
00:24:41,273 --> 00:24:44,651
We should all just put it behind us
and be grateful we're still alive.

335
00:24:47,571 --> 00:24:49,907
Definitely beats the alternative, right?

336
00:24:50,157 --> 00:24:51,950
DENNIS:
I look out at the faces today...

337
00:24:52,159 --> 00:24:55,746
...and I see family members, friends.

338
00:24:56,622 --> 00:25:01,168
But the people that left us on the bridge
that day, they were more than that.

339
00:25:01,793 --> 00:25:03,837
People like Jennifer Alcott...

340
00:25:06,048 --> 00:25:07,424
...Chris Boylan...

341
00:25:09,176 --> 00:25:10,302
...David Buckler.

342
00:25:11,595 --> 00:25:13,555
Maybe you worked next to them.

343
00:25:13,764 --> 00:25:15,432
Maybe you worked for them.

344
00:25:15,641 --> 00:25:19,394
But we all worked with them, huh?

345
00:25:19,603 --> 00:25:22,689
Who can forget Trevor Winn's smile?

346
00:25:25,317 --> 00:25:26,860
Or Isaac Palmer.

347
00:25:27,694 --> 00:25:29,029
Did he just say my name?

348
00:25:29,238 --> 00:25:30,489
[OLIVIA SNORTS]

349
00:25:30,697 --> 00:25:32,616
-That's not funny.
-I know, I'm sorry.

350
00:25:32,824 --> 00:25:35,744
I just get weird with tragedies. I'm sorry.

351
00:25:37,788 --> 00:25:38,914
[WHISPERS]
I see dead people.

352
00:25:39,122 --> 00:25:40,499
[OLIVIA LAUGHING]

353
00:25:40,707 --> 00:25:41,959
Guys.

354
00:25:51,468 --> 00:25:52,678
Death...

355
00:25:55,097 --> 00:25:56,640
...doesn't like to be cheated.

356
00:25:57,307 --> 00:25:58,600
Excuse me?

357
00:25:58,851 --> 00:26:00,185
What's that supposed to mean?

358
00:26:04,857 --> 00:26:07,985
You all just be careful now.

359
00:26:08,193 --> 00:26:10,320
PETER:
Okay. Thanks for the advice!

360
00:26:11,405 --> 00:26:12,489
Creepy guy.

361
00:26:12,698 --> 00:26:15,701
[BLUDWORTH WHISTLING
"LEANING ON THE EVERLASTING ARMS"]

362
00:26:35,387 --> 00:26:38,515
COOK:
How's that foie gras, Sam? Waiting on you.

363
00:26:47,858 --> 00:26:49,193
[TERRY POISON'S "BALLROOM"
PLAYING]

364
00:26:49,401 --> 00:26:52,821
Wasted like a drunk
She drank, drunk, drunk

365
00:26:53,030 --> 00:26:54,740
Stop it

366
00:26:54,948 --> 00:26:56,366
It's not forgotten

367
00:26:57,201 --> 00:26:58,243
COOK 1:
Thanks.

368
00:26:58,452 --> 00:26:59,661
COOK 2:
Got my dessert?

369
00:27:05,042 --> 00:27:06,335
[MIKE CLEARS THROAT]

370
00:27:07,794 --> 00:27:09,046
What's the matter with it?

371
00:27:09,254 --> 00:27:11,465
Said it was flat. No flavor.

372
00:27:12,716 --> 00:27:14,593
-Do they want something else?
MIKE: Yeah.

373
00:27:14,801 --> 00:27:15,969
The check.

374
00:27:18,889 --> 00:27:20,849
Let me taste it.

375
00:27:26,230 --> 00:27:29,733
The customer is an asshole.
The bourguignon is good.

376
00:27:41,995 --> 00:27:43,622
MOLLY:
Hold on.

377
00:27:56,510 --> 00:27:57,803
You mind if I come in?

378
00:27:58,011 --> 00:27:59,930
Yeah. Sure.

379
00:28:10,023 --> 00:28:11,066
Thanks.

380
00:28:11,275 --> 00:28:13,068
I thought you'd be working tonight.

381
00:28:13,277 --> 00:28:16,488
Yeah. You know,
I worked the first shift, but...

382
00:28:17,614 --> 00:28:19,783
...there was something else I needed to do.

383
00:28:21,869 --> 00:28:24,538
[WHISTLING]

384
00:28:25,873 --> 00:28:27,082
-Can I...?
-Oh.

385
00:28:27,291 --> 00:28:29,918
Yeah. Sure, go ahead.

386
00:29:13,962 --> 00:29:16,507
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

387
00:29:23,722 --> 00:29:24,848
Thank you.

388
00:29:26,433 --> 00:29:27,601
Listen....

389
00:29:29,311 --> 00:29:31,813
When everything started going down
on that bridge...

390
00:29:35,067 --> 00:29:37,736
...the only thing I thought about
was you.

391
00:29:38,946 --> 00:29:40,864
Getting you to safety.

392
00:29:41,532 --> 00:29:45,077
You are the only thing
I care about, Molly.

393
00:29:47,871 --> 00:29:50,415
Whatever's wrong, I can fix it.

394
00:29:50,624 --> 00:29:53,043
You haven't done anything wrong.

395
00:29:54,127 --> 00:29:56,046
Then, what? What is it?

396
00:29:57,589 --> 00:29:58,632
Paris.

397
00:29:58,924 --> 00:30:00,342
We talked about that.

398
00:30:00,551 --> 00:30:05,389
I'm not going to uproot my life,
leave you, for that job.

399
00:30:05,597 --> 00:30:08,100
But it's the only thing
you've ever dreamed of.

400
00:30:10,894 --> 00:30:12,771
Life is too short, Sam.

401
00:30:12,980 --> 00:30:15,566
You have to go after what you love.

402
00:30:16,567 --> 00:30:17,776
I am.

403
00:30:22,406 --> 00:30:24,283
You should take the job.

404
00:30:26,243 --> 00:30:28,495
Go to Paris.

405
00:30:44,970 --> 00:30:46,471
-Hey.
CANDICE: Hey.

406
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:48,098
What's the matter?

407
00:30:48,599 --> 00:30:51,727
I don't know. I'm not ready.
I don't feel ready.

408
00:30:51,935 --> 00:30:55,439
It's been really hard to concentrate
after everything.

409
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,774
Yeah? Are you sure?

410
00:30:58,442 --> 00:30:59,735
Yeah.

411
00:30:59,943 --> 00:31:02,821
Because this is the last practice
before the championship.

412
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,449
And it's your last practice
of your college career.

413
00:31:05,657 --> 00:31:07,409
CANDICE:
I know, but....

414
00:31:08,994 --> 00:31:11,246
I think you got this.

415
00:31:12,539 --> 00:31:14,291
-Really?
PETER: Yeah.

416
00:31:15,125 --> 00:31:17,252
I mean, you love it out there.

417
00:31:18,795 --> 00:31:20,255
Okay. You're right.

418
00:31:20,464 --> 00:31:22,674
And besides, coach would kill me. Heh.

419
00:31:22,883 --> 00:31:24,426
Yeah.

420
00:31:24,635 --> 00:31:25,719
Here.

421
00:31:27,804 --> 00:31:29,264
Thanks.

422
00:31:29,473 --> 00:31:30,641
Come here.

423
00:31:33,227 --> 00:31:34,436
Bye.

424
00:31:36,188 --> 00:31:37,981
PETER:
You got this.

425
00:31:47,699 --> 00:31:50,577
MAN 1: You have to get a little more speed.
You gotta hit that follow-up.

426
00:31:54,957 --> 00:31:58,293
GIRL 1: I'm sore from the back extensions.
GIRL 2: Really?

427
00:32:04,174 --> 00:32:05,676
Okay, seriously, this is stupid.

428
00:32:05,884 --> 00:32:08,345
They've gotta make it cooler
or we're gonna pass out.

429
00:32:08,554 --> 00:32:10,055
They're working on it.

430
00:32:10,264 --> 00:32:12,307
CANDICE:
Well, they should have it fixed by now.

431
00:32:12,516 --> 00:32:15,477
[BEEPING]

432
00:32:35,998 --> 00:32:38,375
COACH:
Come on, Candice. You're up.

433
00:32:48,260 --> 00:32:50,053
PETER:
Come on, Candice. You got this.

434
00:33:16,246 --> 00:33:19,374
COACH:
Candice, now.

435
00:33:25,881 --> 00:33:28,926
MAN 1:
Really strong value on this.

436
00:33:40,187 --> 00:33:42,105
GIRL 3:
Hey, coach! How was that?

437
00:34:01,875 --> 00:34:04,878
MAN 1: I wanna see you guys
run the routine all the way through once.

438
00:34:23,188 --> 00:34:24,231
-That's good.
-Whew.

439
00:34:24,438 --> 00:34:26,440
MAN 1:
All right, Janine next. Let's go.

440
00:34:26,650 --> 00:34:28,944
Let's go, ladies, and drink water.

441
00:34:33,866 --> 00:34:34,908
That's it.

442
00:34:35,367 --> 00:34:37,369
Every time, Candice.

443
00:34:42,416 --> 00:34:44,126
-There you go.
-Thanks.

444
00:34:44,333 --> 00:34:46,253
COACH:
Nicely done, Candice.

445
00:34:51,091 --> 00:34:52,592
Okay, go to bars.

446
00:34:52,801 --> 00:34:54,928
WOMAN:
Come on. Hit the floor. You can do it.

447
00:34:57,431 --> 00:34:59,349
PETER:
Go hard this time, Candice.

448
00:35:00,267 --> 00:35:01,685
Let's be aggressive.

449
00:35:02,978 --> 00:35:06,565
COACH:
Here we go, Candice. Stay loose.

450
00:35:07,482 --> 00:35:09,193
MAN 2:
Okay, Porter, it's your turn.

451
00:35:10,444 --> 00:35:12,029
Stay focused.

452
00:35:13,447 --> 00:35:14,698
MAN 3:
Good.

453
00:35:20,787 --> 00:35:22,539
COACH:
Looking good, Candice.

454
00:35:53,904 --> 00:35:56,073
[SCREAMING]

455
00:36:00,244 --> 00:36:02,704
[YELLING]

456
00:36:03,705 --> 00:36:04,748
[GIRLS SCREAMING]

457
00:36:04,957 --> 00:36:06,375
Candice? Candice?!

458
00:36:06,583 --> 00:36:08,877
GIRL 4: Oh, what happened?
MAN 1: Don't touch her.

459
00:36:09,086 --> 00:36:10,712
COACH:
Someone call 911.

460
00:36:10,921 --> 00:36:11,964
Candice?

461
00:36:14,091 --> 00:36:16,468
[AMBULANCE SIREN BEEPS]

462
00:36:19,471 --> 00:36:21,473
[CHATTERING]

463
00:36:33,402 --> 00:36:35,153
Peter.

464
00:36:49,418 --> 00:36:51,253
I came as soon as I heard.

465
00:36:54,923 --> 00:36:56,550
She was doing great.

466
00:36:59,136 --> 00:37:02,598
She was almost finished with her routine
and then....

467
00:37:09,730 --> 00:37:11,607
Why did it happen?

468
00:37:14,318 --> 00:37:16,778
This doesn't make any sense.

469
00:37:16,987 --> 00:37:18,655
I don't know, man.

470
00:37:21,992 --> 00:37:24,494
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry, Peter.

471
00:37:38,091 --> 00:37:40,052
Let's just go, Sam.

472
00:37:54,358 --> 00:37:55,817
Hey.

473
00:37:56,276 --> 00:37:58,028
How's it going?

474
00:37:59,071 --> 00:38:00,948
It's weird.

475
00:38:02,032 --> 00:38:03,575
Being here, I mean.

476
00:38:05,702 --> 00:38:07,538
It's just so quiet.

477
00:38:08,872 --> 00:38:11,875
Yeah, well, Dennis had all the calls
rerouted to corporate.

478
00:38:12,793 --> 00:38:15,879
Yeah, well, it's depressing.

479
00:38:19,383 --> 00:38:22,386
Holy crap. Did you guys
get your bereavement pay yet?

480
00:38:27,057 --> 00:38:28,183
Hey, what's he doing here?

481
00:38:29,017 --> 00:38:31,395
I think he just needed the distraction.

482
00:38:31,603 --> 00:38:33,063
Yeah.

483
00:38:34,022 --> 00:38:35,941
Yeah, that's a bummer about Candice.

484
00:38:36,733 --> 00:38:39,194
Guess we all should have seen
that coming.

485
00:38:41,697 --> 00:38:42,823
What?

486
00:38:43,031 --> 00:38:46,910
You see the crazy shit those gymnasts do.
I'm surprised it doesn't happen more often.

487
00:38:48,287 --> 00:38:50,539
MAN [OVER SPEAKERPHONE]:
Once you've handled the e-mail...

488
00:38:50,747 --> 00:38:53,542
...you'll need to deactivate all the key cards
of the deceased employees.

489
00:38:53,750 --> 00:38:55,252
Instructions are in your binder.

490
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:58,755
Well, shouldn't that be the job
of the facility manager?

491
00:38:59,464 --> 00:39:01,550
The facility manager's dead.

492
00:39:02,217 --> 00:39:03,260
[SIGHS]

493
00:39:03,468 --> 00:39:05,470
Dennis, you want me to fly someone
up there?

494
00:39:05,679 --> 00:39:06,972
No, no, I got it.

495
00:39:14,688 --> 00:39:15,814
Aw, Debbie.

496
00:39:21,778 --> 00:39:23,947
You were so naughty.

497
00:39:33,290 --> 00:39:34,625
[COINS JINGLING]

498
00:39:37,794 --> 00:39:39,129
Fuck it.

499
00:39:46,428 --> 00:39:48,222
Robert, my man.

500
00:39:57,648 --> 00:39:58,941
Ow.

501
00:40:01,527 --> 00:40:02,861
Shit.

502
00:40:09,493 --> 00:40:11,745
You shouldn't have, buddy.

503
00:40:23,131 --> 00:40:24,591
Hey, man, what are you doing up here?

504
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:28,345
Had to get off the factory floor, man.
Roy's driving me crazy.

505
00:40:28,887 --> 00:40:31,682
