759
00:56:21,590 --> 00:56:24,051
Oh, just for some of
our younger patients.

760
00:56:25,802 --> 00:56:29,223
And, um, sometimes our older ones too.
Come on.

761
00:56:37,814 --> 00:56:39,650
[DRONING]

762
00:56:40,025 --> 00:56:41,401
What was that?

763
00:56:41,610 --> 00:56:43,153
Relax.

764
00:56:43,362 --> 00:56:46,156
You know, it looks a lot worse
than it really is.

765
00:56:46,365 --> 00:56:50,661
Okay, I'm gently going to
position your head...

766
00:56:52,246 --> 00:56:53,914
...and I want you to tell me...

767
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:56,875
...when this feels snug.

768
00:56:57,084 --> 00:56:58,460
I can't move my head.

769
00:56:58,669 --> 00:57:01,505
Perfect. Just what we want.

770
00:57:03,507 --> 00:57:05,384
There we go.

771
00:57:05,592 --> 00:57:09,221
Okay, now comes the fun part.
Here comes a drop.

772
00:57:09,972 --> 00:57:13,767
And you will feel a little numbness
in your eye...

773
00:57:13,976 --> 00:57:15,435
...which is a good thing.

774
00:57:31,493 --> 00:57:32,786
Deep breath.

775
00:57:37,416 --> 00:57:38,834
Relax.

776
00:57:45,591 --> 00:57:46,675
Very good.

777
00:57:53,056 --> 00:57:54,558
Thattagirl.

778
00:58:03,901 --> 00:58:05,194
There.

779
00:58:05,402 --> 00:58:08,155
That's not so bad, is it?

780
00:58:20,250 --> 00:58:21,752
Looks good.

781
00:58:28,842 --> 00:58:29,885
[CREAKING]

782
00:58:30,093 --> 00:58:32,179
-What was that?
-Just relax, Olivia.

783
00:58:32,387 --> 00:58:34,848
I'm just gonna enter some data into....

784
00:58:39,144 --> 00:58:40,354
Dottie!

785
00:58:41,730 --> 00:58:43,065
Dot--

786
00:58:43,273 --> 00:58:45,901
Do you know what?
My assistant's given me an incomplete file.

787
00:58:46,109 --> 00:58:47,861
I'll be right back.

788
00:58:49,738 --> 00:58:51,949
OLIVIA:
Hold on, you're leaving?!

789
00:59:15,514 --> 00:59:18,517
[BEEPING]

790
00:59:22,312 --> 00:59:25,315
Is that supposed to be happening?!

791
00:59:32,072 --> 00:59:34,491
[BEEPING FASTER]

792
00:59:49,840 --> 00:59:52,718
[WHIMPERING]

793
00:59:54,887 --> 00:59:56,889
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

794
00:59:57,848 --> 01:00:00,267
[SCREAMING]

795
01:00:05,522 --> 01:00:06,857
Help me!

796
01:00:18,827 --> 01:00:20,454
Olivia Castle. Where is she?

797
01:00:20,662 --> 01:00:21,747
SAM:
She might be in danger.

798
01:00:21,955 --> 01:00:24,291
She's fine.
We do this kind of procedure all the time.

799
01:00:24,499 --> 01:00:26,418
[OLIVIA SCREAMING]

800
01:00:27,836 --> 01:00:28,921
[SOBBING]

801
01:00:32,382 --> 01:00:34,551
Help me!

802
01:00:35,260 --> 01:00:36,845
Help me!

803
01:00:37,596 --> 01:00:40,599
[SCREAMING]

804
01:00:55,322 --> 01:00:57,115
DOTTIE:
This has never happened before.

805
01:00:57,324 --> 01:00:59,451
[DOTTIE &amp; DETECTIVE
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

806
01:01:01,912 --> 01:01:03,539
Sam.

807
01:01:04,581 --> 01:01:06,917
Stay with me tonight, please.

808
01:01:08,043 --> 01:01:09,878
Of course.

809
01:01:14,758 --> 01:01:16,760
Five different systems had to go wrong...

810
01:01:16,969 --> 01:01:20,806
...for that laser to fail us
so spectacularly. Five.

811
01:01:21,014 --> 01:01:22,724
What do you want from us?

812
01:01:22,933 --> 01:01:25,185
I want you to tell me
what you think is going on.

813
01:01:25,394 --> 01:01:28,063
Two deaths? Okay, all right.
That's a coincidence.

814
01:01:28,272 --> 01:01:31,149
Three? That's a pattern.

815
01:01:44,162 --> 01:01:45,622
Now...

816
01:01:46,373 --> 01:01:48,625
...I know you two didn't do this.

817
01:01:49,877 --> 01:01:51,128
All right?

818
01:01:52,546 --> 01:01:54,923
But I think you know something.

819
01:01:57,593 --> 01:01:58,760
What is it?

820
01:02:00,846 --> 01:02:03,307
We don't know anything.

821
01:02:03,932 --> 01:02:06,185
Take a guess.

822
01:02:12,024 --> 01:02:15,527
We think we weren't supposed to survive
on that bridge.

823
01:02:16,862 --> 01:02:17,905
What?

824
01:02:18,572 --> 01:02:22,868
And now something
is trying to set it right.

825
01:02:24,369 --> 01:02:26,121
"Something"?

826
01:02:27,915 --> 01:02:29,458
That's all you got?

827
01:02:29,666 --> 01:02:30,918
SAM:
Right now, yeah.

828
01:02:31,877 --> 01:02:36,548
But if you come up
with any other explanations, let us know.

829
01:02:39,218 --> 01:02:41,345
Thank you.

830
01:02:47,559 --> 01:02:49,353
"Something."

831
01:02:58,278 --> 01:02:59,446
Hey.

832
01:03:01,448 --> 01:03:02,866
Been up long?

833
01:03:04,993 --> 01:03:09,665
Uh, I don't know. I couldn't sleep.
I just kept thinking about the bridge.

834
01:03:13,460 --> 01:03:16,296
Sam, you can't do this to yourself.

835
01:03:16,505 --> 01:03:20,467
No. No, no, no. I was thinking about,
in the premonition...

836
01:03:21,301 --> 01:03:25,389
...we all got off the bus,
but the ground gave way and Candice fell.

837
01:03:26,723 --> 01:03:28,517
Then the bus tipped over.

838
01:03:29,643 --> 01:03:32,646
And Isaac, he never got off the bus.
He went with it.

839
01:03:32,855 --> 01:03:34,189
What are you getting at?

840
01:03:34,398 --> 01:03:37,526
I know that there was just
so much going on....

841
01:03:38,527 --> 01:03:41,405
Look, I know that I helped you across.

842
01:03:41,947 --> 01:03:44,741
Then I reached back for Olivia.

843
01:03:45,367 --> 01:03:47,703
But she didn't make it. She fell.

844
01:03:50,205 --> 01:03:52,916
So first was Candice.

845
01:03:53,125 --> 01:03:54,459
[SCREAMS]

846
01:03:55,794 --> 01:03:56,837
Then Isaac.

847
01:03:58,172 --> 01:03:59,214
Then Olivia.

848
01:03:59,423 --> 01:04:00,591
[SCREAMS]

849
01:04:00,799 --> 01:04:02,551
They're dying in order.

850
01:04:03,802 --> 01:04:05,554
Who dies after Olivia?

851
01:04:29,620 --> 01:04:30,954
[SIGHS]

852
01:04:41,006 --> 01:04:43,592
NATHAN [OVER PA]: Roy, would you come
to the control room, please?

853
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:46,512
MAN: Uh-oh, Roy, that's the boss.
You in trouble, Roy.

854
01:05:03,070 --> 01:05:05,280
ROY: Okay, schoolboy,
what do you wanna talk to me about?

855
01:05:05,489 --> 01:05:08,242
NATHAN: What is with your timecard?
ROY: Let's talk about my timecard.

856
01:05:08,450 --> 01:05:10,869
You cut my hours,
which means you cut my pay!

857
01:05:11,078 --> 01:05:12,204
I cut everyone's hours, okay?

858
01:05:12,412 --> 01:05:15,457
Corporate has us operating at less than
50 percent until this thing blows over.

859
01:05:15,666 --> 01:05:17,626
My bookie ain't operating at 50 percent.

860
01:05:17,835 --> 01:05:20,337
-My dumb kid ain't operating at 50 percent.
-Roy.

861
01:05:20,546 --> 01:05:23,590
My ex-wife, she's taking 50 percent,
so I'll tell you what I'm gonna do.

862
01:05:23,799 --> 01:05:24,883
No, we gotta move, man.

863
01:05:25,092 --> 01:05:28,387
ROY: Hey, I'm not going anywhere. Hey!
NATHAN: Look, we gotta move! Gotta move!

864
01:05:28,595 --> 01:05:29,888
We gotta move now!

865
01:05:31,723 --> 01:05:34,142
[ROY GRUNTS THEN SCREAMS]

866
01:05:39,982 --> 01:05:42,234
NATHAN:
Roy! You okay down there?

867
01:05:46,947 --> 01:05:48,448
-Hey, Dennis?
DENNIS: Hey.

868
01:05:50,617 --> 01:05:52,536
They're closing us down.

869
01:05:52,744 --> 01:05:53,996
They're shutting down the plant?

870
01:05:54,204 --> 01:05:58,458
Not the plant, just us.
Just sales and administration.

871
01:05:58,667 --> 01:06:00,294
Can you believe it? Us?

872
01:06:00,502 --> 01:06:02,629
It's the factory guys
that usually get laid off.

873
01:06:02,838 --> 01:06:04,339
Not us, we're supposed to be safe.

874
01:06:04,548 --> 01:06:06,884
Yeah, Dennis, we got bigger problems.

875
01:06:07,759 --> 01:06:09,511
Olivia and Isaac are dead.

876
01:06:10,512 --> 01:06:11,555
Who's Isaac?

877
01:06:11,763 --> 01:06:14,850
Isaac Palmer, tech support.

878
01:06:15,893 --> 01:06:17,144
Wasn't he dead already?

879
01:06:17,352 --> 01:06:18,687
No, Dennis.

880
01:06:18,896 --> 01:06:24,234
Listen, it's going to happen to us too
if we don't do something about it.

881
01:06:24,860 --> 01:06:28,155
Yeah, I understand.
Listen, it's called survivor's guilt.

882
01:06:28,363 --> 01:06:32,409
No. No, guilt doesn't kill you.

883
01:06:32,618 --> 01:06:34,536
Obviously, you've never met my in-laws.

884
01:06:34,745 --> 01:06:36,538
I'm not fucking around here, Dennis.

885
01:06:36,997 --> 01:06:38,540
Anyone could be next.

886
01:06:38,749 --> 01:06:41,335
It could be you. Understand?

887
01:06:41,543 --> 01:06:42,961
Nobody's safe.

888
01:06:43,170 --> 01:06:44,713
What are you talking about?

889
01:06:47,007 --> 01:06:49,676
We weren't supposed to survive
that bridge collapse.

890
01:06:49,885 --> 01:06:52,763
And so now it's kill or be killed.

891
01:06:53,347 --> 01:06:55,516
You get that, Dennis?

892
01:06:56,600 --> 01:06:57,643
Whatever.

893
01:06:57,851 --> 01:07:00,687
I warned you.
Do whatever you wanna do.

894
01:07:02,731 --> 01:07:03,815
[DOOR CLOSES]

895
01:07:04,525 --> 01:07:06,235
I will.

896
01:07:11,031 --> 01:07:13,283
Hey, Agent Block, it's Dennis. Um--

897
01:07:13,492 --> 01:07:17,371
Listen, Pete just came in here
and he's just completely lost it.

898
01:07:17,579 --> 01:07:20,415
He's yelling about "kill or be killed."

899
01:07:20,624 --> 01:07:23,544
Oh, yeah,
it definitely sounded like a threat.

900
01:07:40,477 --> 01:07:41,562
What happened?

901
01:07:41,770 --> 01:07:44,648
NATHAN: I don't know. I don't know.
It just happened so fast.

902
01:07:44,857 --> 01:07:47,526
-Nathan. Are you okay?
-Yeah.

903
01:07:47,734 --> 01:07:51,405
-We heard, and we thought--
-No. No, uh, I'm good.

904
01:07:52,531 --> 01:07:53,782
Did you kill him?

905
01:07:54,157 --> 01:07:55,242
What?

906
01:07:55,450 --> 01:07:57,995
No. No, I just--

907
01:07:58,203 --> 01:08:01,039
It was just timing, you know?
He got in the way and--

908
01:08:01,248 --> 01:08:02,499
No, you did, didn't you?

909
01:08:02,708 --> 01:08:06,044
You saw it coming, and then you took
his life. You put him in the way.

910
01:08:06,253 --> 01:08:07,838
No, I didn't really do anything.

911
01:08:08,046 --> 01:08:10,841
-Tell us the truth: Did you or didn't you?
-Hey, Peter, calm down.

912
01:08:11,049 --> 01:08:12,426
Did you or didn't you?

913
01:08:15,262 --> 01:08:17,305
Did you or didn't you?

914
01:08:18,223 --> 01:08:21,143
Yes. I think I did.

915
01:08:21,977 --> 01:08:23,228
I killed him.

916
01:08:24,145 --> 01:08:27,274
So if the theory works,
then you traded spots.

917
01:08:27,482 --> 01:08:31,153
He should have your death,
and you should have his years.

918
01:08:31,904 --> 01:08:33,154
How do we know for sure?

919
01:08:33,363 --> 01:08:35,240
I think there's an order to these deaths.

920
01:08:36,658 --> 01:08:39,578
They mirror the order everyone died in
on the bridge.

921
01:08:39,786 --> 01:08:41,537
Then who would be next?

922
01:08:43,415 --> 01:08:45,667
Who wants to be first to tell me
what the hell happened?

923
01:08:46,084 --> 01:08:47,127
Who is it, Sam?

924
01:08:47,336 --> 01:08:48,377
Who's what?

925
01:08:50,005 --> 01:08:52,799
[ALL GASPING]

926
01:08:53,675 --> 01:08:56,178
Dennis! It was Dennis.

927
01:08:56,636 --> 01:08:58,596
No shit.

928
01:08:59,640 --> 01:09:01,390
MAN:
Jesus.

929
01:09:04,645 --> 01:09:06,438
Why are you fighting me on this?

930
01:09:06,647 --> 01:09:08,982
You're not seriously going to work,
are you?

931
01:09:09,191 --> 01:09:13,444
Molly, Isaac died on a massage table.

932
01:09:13,654 --> 01:09:16,281
If Death is gonna come for me,
I don't think it matters where I am.

933
01:09:16,490 --> 01:09:18,200
You have to do something.

934
01:09:18,408 --> 01:09:21,118
-What, kill someone so I can live?
-No, of course not.

935
01:09:21,912 --> 01:09:23,997
We'll just have to
figure something else out.

936
01:09:24,206 --> 01:09:26,250
I have figured it out.

937
01:09:26,750 --> 01:09:29,670
Something saved me on that bridge.

938
01:09:29,877 --> 01:09:31,712
Maybe it doesn't want me to die.

939
01:09:34,049 --> 01:09:35,466
Maybe.

940
01:09:35,676 --> 01:09:38,554
We can't live our lives in fear, Moll.

941
01:09:40,930 --> 01:09:45,185
So if it happens tomorrow,
or 50 years from now, whatever.

942
01:09:45,394 --> 01:09:47,604
As long as we're together...

943
01:09:48,856 --> 01:09:50,064
...I'll be okay.

944
01:09:52,776 --> 01:09:55,571
Right? Why don't you come by
after my shift...

945
01:09:55,779 --> 01:09:57,865
...and I'll make you
a nice late dinner, okay?

946
01:10:06,623 --> 01:10:08,000
All right, give me this.

947
01:10:11,253 --> 01:10:13,088
[SIGHS]

948
01:10:13,297 --> 01:10:15,299
[CHATTERING]

949
01:10:16,967 --> 01:10:19,178
WOMAN: Excuse me.
We don't have to wait for them, do we?

950
01:10:19,386 --> 01:10:21,638
HOSTESS: I'll let you know.
WOMAN: Okay, thank you.

951
01:10:21,847 --> 01:10:24,266
[TERRY POISON'S "GIRL ON THE RUN"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

952
01:10:24,474 --> 01:10:26,768
To the girl on the run

953
01:10:26,977 --> 01:10:30,022
[SINGER SINGING IN FRENCH]

954
01:10:37,404 --> 01:10:38,822
COOK 1:
Veal's ready, take it out.

955
01:10:39,031 --> 01:10:41,074
Samuel. Get to work on the bourguignon.

956
01:10:41,283 --> 01:10:42,743
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

957
01:10:49,458 --> 01:10:50,667
Whoa.

958
01:10:51,084 --> 01:10:52,127
COOK 2:
Pan coming through.

959
01:10:53,754 --> 01:10:55,422
COOK 3:
Whoa, watch yourself.

960
01:11:06,183 --> 01:11:08,519
MANAGER: Okay. Meat's in. Pick it up, eh?
COOK 4: Yes, sir.

961
01:11:19,363 --> 01:11:20,989
Whoa.

962
01:11:21,198 --> 01:11:23,033
That could've been ugly, huh? Ha, ha.

963
01:11:23,242 --> 01:11:25,869
Yeah. Could've been.

964
01:11:30,916 --> 01:11:32,292
Vincent, speed it up, okay?

965
01:11:39,633 --> 01:11:40,843
SAM:
Whoa, hey!

966
01:11:41,051 --> 01:11:42,094
[SPUTTERING]

967
01:11:56,358 --> 01:11:57,401
[SIGHS]

968
01:12:04,491 --> 01:12:06,493
CHEF:
Hey, clean that grate.

969
01:12:14,960 --> 01:12:17,921
-Just met your girlfriend.
-Oh.

970
01:12:18,130 --> 01:12:21,049
Are you sure it's okay
if I make her a little something?

971
01:12:21,675 --> 01:12:23,677
Make sure to clean up afterward.

972
01:12:23,886 --> 01:12:26,638
I will, of course. Thank you.

973
01:12:27,931 --> 01:12:29,224
And, chef....

974
01:12:29,433 --> 01:12:30,684
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

975
01:12:30,893 --> 01:12:32,728
The apprenticeship.

976
01:12:32,936 --> 01:12:35,397
If the offer still stands...

977
01:12:35,606 --> 01:12:36,940
...I'd like to take it.

978
01:12:38,609 --> 01:12:40,110
It's yours.

979
01:12:44,698 --> 01:12:47,826
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

980
01:12:54,791 --> 01:12:56,251
SAM:
Okay, no more suspense.

981
01:12:56,460 --> 01:12:57,878
[MOLLY CHUCKLES]

982
01:12:58,086 --> 01:13:00,130
What you've been waiting for.

983
01:13:01,882 --> 01:13:04,301
Wow. You're gonna help me
with this, right?

984
01:13:04,510 --> 01:13:05,928
Yeah, sure, if you want me to--

985
01:13:06,136 --> 01:13:07,638
No? You don't want me to...?

986
01:13:08,430 --> 01:13:09,598
So how's your French?

987
01:13:10,098 --> 01:13:12,267
Heh. Terrible.

988
01:13:12,476 --> 01:13:16,104
Oh, good. Well, then,
we can be terrible together.

989
01:13:16,313 --> 01:13:19,483
-Why?
-I took the internship.

990
01:13:19,691 --> 01:13:23,612
What? Sam, that's amazing.

991
01:13:26,990 --> 01:13:28,784
I'm so proud of you.

992
01:13:45,968 --> 01:13:48,679
-Peter.
-Hey.

993
01:13:50,514 --> 01:13:53,475
You okay, man?
You look a little, uh, upset.

994
01:13:53,684 --> 01:13:57,646
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Just a rough couple days.

995
01:13:58,355 --> 01:14:01,024
Yeah. Yeah, for everyone.

996
01:14:01,984 --> 01:14:03,861
For some more than others.

997
01:14:04,653 --> 01:14:06,029
Do you mind if I come in?

998
01:14:06,238 --> 01:14:08,574
Oh, yeah, of course. Yeah, come in.

999
01:14:14,246 --> 01:14:15,706
Here, have a seat.

1000
01:14:16,582 --> 01:14:18,166
Thanks.

1001
01:14:22,337 --> 01:14:23,589
Hey, Peter.

1002
01:14:24,715 --> 01:14:26,550
Hi, Molly.

1003
01:14:41,356 --> 01:14:45,152
Peter, can I get you anything to eat?
I can make you up some pasta.

1004
01:14:45,736 --> 01:14:49,281
Uh, no. No, no, no. I'm good.
Uh, thank you.

1005
01:14:50,782 --> 01:14:52,576
Uh, I'm sorry. I just thought--

1006
01:14:52,784 --> 01:14:55,370
It's good that you're here.
You shouldn't be alone right now.

1007
01:14:55,996 --> 01:14:58,415
Yeah, you know,
I'm surprised I'm here at all.

1008
01:14:59,875 --> 01:15:01,251
Uh....

1009
01:15:01,460 --> 01:15:03,212
Still alive, I mean.

1010
01:15:03,420 --> 01:15:04,755
I'm next to go, right?

1011
01:15:06,089 --> 01:15:07,758
It's me and then you, isn't it?

1012
01:15:10,594 --> 01:15:15,390
Anyways, uh, I was up all last night,
you know...

1013
01:15:15,599 --> 01:15:18,769
...thinking about if I could really do it.

1014
01:15:19,394 --> 01:15:23,148
-Do what?
-Take someone else's life.

1015
01:15:23,357 --> 01:15:28,612
If I could actually kill some stranger,
replace their life with my own.

1016
01:15:29,571 --> 01:15:31,448
And I thought about it.

1017
01:15:32,282 --> 01:15:34,284
And I convinced myself that...

1018
01:15:35,619 --> 01:15:37,162
...yeah, I could.

1019
01:15:39,790 --> 01:15:42,209
So I went on a walk.

1020
01:15:42,417 --> 01:15:45,087
You know, nowhere in particular...

1021
01:15:45,295 --> 01:15:48,173
...but every couple of minutes,
an opportunity would just present itself.

1022
01:15:48,382 --> 01:15:51,134
Heh. Like clockwork.

1023
01:15:51,593 --> 01:15:54,638
I could just grab somebody
and pull them into an alley.

1024
01:15:55,264 --> 01:15:58,809
Or just shove somebody off a curb
into traffic.

1025
01:15:59,601 --> 01:16:01,019
You know?

1026
01:16:01,854 --> 01:16:03,146
It'd be real easy.

1027
01:16:06,191 --> 01:16:08,443
Peter, what did you do?

1028
01:16:16,159 --> 01:16:18,579
-Did you...?
-No, I didn't.

1029
01:16:21,498 --> 01:16:23,500
I couldn't.

1030
01:16:23,709 --> 01:16:25,502
I realized that...

1031
01:16:25,711 --> 01:16:28,630
...I couldn't kill somebody
that didn't deserve to die.

1032
01:16:30,716 --> 01:16:34,428
And I thought about Candice,
and I thought, "Wait a minute.

1033
01:16:35,470 --> 01:16:38,348
Candice didn't deserve to die.

1034
01:16:40,350 --> 01:16:43,103
Olivia didn't. Dennis didn't.

1035
01:16:43,896 --> 01:16:45,480
I don't."

1036
01:16:47,357 --> 01:16:48,692
Do I?

1037
01:16:48,901 --> 01:16:51,069
No, of course you don't.

1038
01:16:54,031 --> 01:16:55,449
Well...

1039
01:16:56,617 --> 01:17:02,706
...none of us deserve to die,
then why is it...

1040
01:17:04,041 --> 01:17:07,002
...that you deserve to live, Molly?

1041
01:17:08,921 --> 01:17:10,214
You said it yourself...

1042
01:17:11,381 --> 01:17:12,549
...you don't.

1043
01:17:15,427 --> 01:17:16,595
[GUNSHOT]

1044
01:17:18,263 --> 01:17:19,681
Go!

1045
01:17:20,390 --> 01:17:24,978
Repeat, shots fired.
Requesting backup. 1026 Washington.

1046
01:17:25,729 --> 01:17:29,107
Hide and I'll distract him.
When you can, go.

1047
01:17:31,235 --> 01:17:32,694
PETER:
Not done yet, Sam.

1048
01:17:35,364 --> 01:17:36,657
Where is she?

1049
01:17:38,700 --> 01:17:42,454
-Where is she?!
-I'm not gonna let you hurt her, Peter.

1050
01:17:42,663 --> 01:17:44,456
You're gonna have to kill me first.

1051
01:17:44,665 --> 01:17:46,792
Well, that doesn't do me any good.
Heh, heh.

1052
01:17:47,000 --> 01:17:48,210
Death's after you too.

1053
01:17:48,418 --> 01:17:50,754
This is crazy, Peter. Don't do this.

1054
01:17:51,922 --> 01:17:55,509
Just think for a minute, all right?

1055
01:17:55,717 --> 01:17:57,302
You are not a killer.

1056
01:17:58,679 --> 01:18:00,305
I don't wanna kill anybody, Sam.

1057
01:18:03,684 --> 01:18:04,852
I don't wanna die yet either.

1058
01:18:05,060 --> 01:18:06,436
[BOTH GRUNT]

1059
01:18:11,775 --> 01:18:14,111
Heh. It's not your time yet.

1060
01:18:23,120 --> 01:18:25,289
Don't worry, Molly...

1061
01:18:27,457 --> 01:18:29,001
...I didn't kill him.

1062
01:18:31,461 --> 01:18:35,132
But I didn't need to, Molly...

1063
01:18:36,258 --> 01:18:40,304
...because Death
is gonna do that for me.

1064
01:18:40,804 --> 01:18:43,140
Doesn't mean I can't help it.

1065
01:18:45,142 --> 01:18:46,810
That's it.

1066
01:19:28,519 --> 01:19:31,730
-Are you okay? What's going on?
-It's Peter. He has a gun.

1067
01:19:31,939 --> 01:19:33,440
[GUNFIRE]

1068
01:19:37,027 --> 01:19:38,695
Oh, my God.

1069
01:19:42,074 --> 01:19:43,784
You killed him.

1070
01:19:51,166 --> 01:19:52,668
It's Sam's turn.

1071
01:19:58,715 --> 01:20:01,218
MOLLY:
Peter, just go.

1072
01:20:01,593 --> 01:20:04,805
You have Block's life, you're safe now.

1073
01:20:05,681 --> 01:20:07,140
Please.

1074
01:20:07,391 --> 01:20:09,226
I'm sorry, Molly.

1075
01:20:11,436 --> 01:20:14,189
But you just witnessed the murder
of a federal agent.

1076
01:20:16,859 --> 01:20:21,363
And I'm not gonna spend
the life I just earned in prison.

1077
01:20:22,489 --> 01:20:23,699
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

1078
01:20:27,119 --> 01:20:30,372
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1079
01:20:32,833 --> 01:20:35,419
Molly, go! Go get help!

1080
01:21:03,238 --> 01:21:05,616
You son of a bitch!

1081
01:21:43,654 --> 01:21:46,865
Tell Candice I love her.

1082
01:21:47,241 --> 01:21:48,283
Peter.

1083
01:22:14,226 --> 01:22:17,396
It's gone. You killed him.

1084
01:22:18,188 --> 01:22:20,023
So does that mean I get Block's life?

1085
01:22:20,858 --> 01:22:22,276
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

1086
01:22:25,028 --> 01:22:26,530
Yeah.

1087
01:22:27,197 --> 01:22:29,116
I guess I do.

1088
01:22:45,090 --> 01:22:46,592
Do you mind if I take the window seat?

1089
01:22:47,009 --> 01:22:50,012
-You're gonna make me sit in the middle?
-Uh-huh.

1090
01:22:50,220 --> 01:22:52,347
SAM: I'm like twice your size.
-Not really.

1091
01:22:52,556 --> 01:22:54,516
-All right.
MAN 1: Sit down.

1092
01:22:54,725 --> 01:22:57,019
MAN 2: I'll remove him.
GUY: Fuck you. I'll remove myself.

1093
01:22:57,227 --> 01:22:58,353
GIRL:
Get off him!

1094
01:22:58,562 --> 01:22:59,813
Settle down!

1095
01:23:00,022 --> 01:23:02,858
-Come on, Browning! Come on, you punk!
-Get off the plane!

1096
01:23:03,066 --> 01:23:05,485
Get off the plane. You don't understand!

1097
01:23:05,694 --> 01:23:07,404
LEWTON:
Everybody just stay where you are.

1098
01:23:09,698 --> 01:23:13,285
-What's all that about?
-I have no idea.

1099
01:23:13,493 --> 01:23:16,538
PILOT [OVER PA]: Ladies and gentlemen,
we'll be pulling away from the gate as--

1100
01:23:16,747 --> 01:23:18,081
[STATIC CRACKLES OVER PA]

1101
01:23:22,711 --> 01:23:23,795
MOLLY:
Here we go.

1102
01:23:24,004 --> 01:23:26,507
WOMAN 1 [OVER PA]: The cabin lights
have been dimmed for takeoff.

1103
01:23:26,715 --> 01:23:29,384
[MAN 3 SPEAKING IN FRENCH OVER PA]

1104
01:23:49,613 --> 01:23:51,532
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

1105
01:23:51,740 --> 01:23:54,326
With curiosity

1106
01:23:55,744 --> 01:23:59,206
Dust in the wind

1107
01:24:04,378 --> 01:24:05,671
[MOLLY GASPS]

1108
01:24:11,426 --> 01:24:12,636
Sorry about that.

1109
01:24:14,972 --> 01:24:17,224
WOMAN 2:
Oh, excuse me.

1110
01:24:17,432 --> 01:24:22,062
Those passengers who got off the plane
earlier, what was that all about?

1111
01:24:22,271 --> 01:24:24,940
FLIGHT ATTENDANT: A kid had
a panic attack and wanted off the plane.

1112
01:24:25,274 --> 01:24:27,192
Said he had some kind of vision.

1113
01:24:28,068 --> 01:24:29,403
No.

1114
01:24:31,488 --> 01:24:32,614
Oh, my God!

1115
01:24:34,908 --> 01:24:36,827
[PASSENGERS SCREAMING]

1116
01:24:37,536 --> 01:24:38,579
Sam.

1117
01:24:58,849 --> 01:25:00,309
[SCREAMING]

1118
01:25:04,271 --> 01:25:06,982
[MOLLY SCREAMING]

1119
01:25:07,191 --> 01:25:08,358
SAM:
I got you!

1120
01:25:10,527 --> 01:25:13,488
-Sam!
-Molly, hold on!

1121
01:25:15,032 --> 01:25:16,074
No!

1122
01:25:16,283 --> 01:25:17,576
[SCREAMS]

1123
01:25:18,160 --> 01:25:19,828
No!

1124
01:25:22,122 --> 01:25:24,458
[SAM SCREAMING IN SLOW MOTION]

1125
01:25:33,842 --> 01:25:35,844
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

1126
01:25:36,053 --> 01:25:38,889
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1127
01:25:44,186 --> 01:25:45,687
Nice of you to come, Nathan.

1128
01:25:45,896 --> 01:25:48,148
I know Roy
wasn't the easiest guy to work with.

1129
01:25:49,233 --> 01:25:50,567
You know.

1130
01:25:50,776 --> 01:25:52,861
I still can't believe he's gone, though.

1131
01:25:53,070 --> 01:25:55,489
Yeah. Yeah, no kidding.

1132
01:25:55,697 --> 01:25:56,949
I guess it was for the best.

1133
01:25:58,367 --> 01:25:59,409
What do you mean?

1134
01:25:59,618 --> 01:26:02,746
Company did an autopsy
for insurance purposes.

1135
01:26:02,955 --> 01:26:05,999
Turns out Roy had an enlarged
blood vessel in his brain so big...

1136
01:26:06,208 --> 01:26:09,419
...it was about to burst.
They said he'd be dead any day now.

1137
01:26:09,628 --> 01:26:11,880
[OVER SPEAKERS]
Nothing lasts forever but the....

1138
01:26:12,089 --> 01:26:13,757
Any day?

1139
01:26:14,675 --> 01:26:15,717
Life's a bitch.

1140
01:26:15,926 --> 01:26:17,719
Dust in the wind

1141
01:26:29,940 --> 01:26:31,316
[SCREAMS]

1142
01:26:33,485 --> 01:26:34,611
[TIRES SCREECH]

1143
01:26:38,657 --> 01:26:39,783
[GROANS]

1144
01:26:39,992 --> 01:26:41,076
[GROANS]

1145
01:27:10,230 --> 01:27:11,315
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

1146
01:27:28,373 --> 01:27:29,625
[SCREAMS]

1147
01:27:45,140 --> 01:27:46,767
[YELLS]

1148
01:27:58,153 --> 01:28:01,406
BLUDWORTH:
You all just be careful now.

1149
01:31:44,838 --> 01:31:46,840
[English - US - SDH]
